Traditional dye-doped fluorescent graphene oxide (GO) reveals a low quantum 
yield and a short life expectancy. Herein, red-luminescent silica-coated Eu(3+) 
complex nanoparticles were synthesized and covalently coupled to GO nanosheets 
by means of a carbodiimide-mediated amidation process. SEM and TEM studies 
